Chroot with non root

debootstrap --arch i386 --foreign sid ./i386
http://mirrors.aliyun.com/debian

chroot ./i386 /usr/bin

/debootstrap/debootstrap --second-stage

exit
chmod 0755 ./i386 -R
unshare -mr /usr/sbin/chroot ./i386 /bin/bash


https://github.com/nix-community/nix-user-chroot
Check if your kernel supports user namespaces for unprivileged users
$ unshare --user --pid echo YES

